  "prob_desc_description": "While playing with geometric figures Alex has accidentally invented a concept of a $$$n$$$-th order rhombus in a cell grid.A $$$1$$$-st order rhombus is just a square $$$1 \\times 1$$$ (i.e just a cell).A $$$n$$$-th order rhombus for all $$$n \\geq 2$$$ one obtains from a $$$n-1$$$-th order rhombus adding all cells which have a common side with it to it (look at the picture to understand it better).    Alex asks you to compute the number of cells in a $$$n$$$-th order rhombus.",
